\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 Literature is, surely, tied to cultural capital. But it is also tied to pleasure, and potentially to love. When we discuss literature with others, we enter capital\'92s world; one may wish to seem erudite, or one may wish to seem \'93hip,\'94 and one may present a particular literary \'91face\'92 accordingly. But the literature one discusses need not align too closely with the literature one loves. [This is too bland/generic, but also possibly getting toward the important thing]}